&lt;p&gt;In this episode we discuss the first edition of &lt;a href="http://www.boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/10547/betrayal-at-house-on-the-hill" target="_blank"&gt;Betrayal at the House on the Hill&lt;/a&gt; with designer Professor Bruce Glassco. Our talk revolves around the strong genre feel of the game, the complexities of designing games with multiple adventures, and the intrigues of games that are a mix between cooperate and competitive. We also learn that Bruce is a literature professor specializing in 19th Century American and British literature.&lt;/p&gt;
