&lt;p&gt;During this episode we discuss &lt;a href="http://www.forrest-pruzan.com/portfolio_frames.html" target="_blank"&gt;Hoopla&lt;/a&gt;, a Cranium licensed game design by Forest-Pruzan Creative. Speaking with Alan Pruzan, one of the inventors of the game, we explore the intracacies of designing a game that is remarkably different from its license, but captures the same feeling of the licensed product. Our discussions range from the complexities of paring down a game with a larger scope to what Hoopla brings to the Cranium universe.&lt;/p&gt;
