			<title>NvP 2x01 - Minimus with Ken Burnside</title>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/NinjaVsPirates/~3/1KV5aEShsD0/nv_p_2x01_minimus_with_ken_burnside</link>
            <description>Ken Burnside is the creative director at &lt;a href="http://www.adastragames.com"&gt;Ad Astra Games&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.adastragames.com/downloads/RPGs/Minimus.pdf"&gt;Minimus&lt;/a&gt; is a 4 page role playing game (RPG) that is a complete generic roleplaying system. It has everything to cover all the standard DnD situations, minus the spell lists and etc. The interesting thing is the collaborative character creation system and the goal driven reward system.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;We focus our discussion with Ken on the way he used his mechanics to foster the dynamics he considers to be key to a good role play session.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;

